00:19:26,9 --> 00:19:28,768
drifting.
And we had all reason to

345
00:19:28,768 --> 00:19:31,767
believe that the balloon would
drift somewhere in this

346
00:19:31,767 --> 00:19:33,804
direction.
And we alerted these radar

347
00:19:33,804 --> 00:19:35,898
stations.
These circles here are radar

348
00:19:35,898 --> 00:19:38,105
stations.
Because there are no airfields

349
00:19:38,105 --> 00:19:40,596
here in Australia.
And so we knew we couldn't

350
00:19:40,596 --> 00:19:43,142
follow the balloon.
We would probably lose it.

351
00:19:43,142 --> 00:19:45,689
And therefore we alerted these
radar stations.

352
00:19:45,689 --> 00:19:48,688
They could tell us then when
the balloon was in sight.

353
00:19:48,688 --> 00:19:51,348
And that would allow us then to
cut the balloon,

354
00:19:51,348 --> 00:19:55,543
cut the payload loose and --
